What are policies, what is the purpose of it?
Policy is an standard language written in Json format, contains collection of permissions applicable for a resource or service that can be assigned to a IAM User or group in enforcing the restrictions

There are 3 types of policies are there
1. AWS Managed Policies
2. Customer Managed Policies
3. Inline policies

How to define our own policy definition?
A policy definition contains 5 sections
1. sid = unique name assigned to a policy to identify or distinguish from other
2. principle = this policy can be applied to whom (arn of a user or group)
3. action = permissions to be granted to a user/group
4. effect = allow/denied
5. resource = it can be applied to which resource/service

{
	"Version": "",
	"Statement": [
		{
		"Sid": "",
		"Effect": "",
		"Action": [
		
		],
		"Principle": "",
		"Resource":""
		}
	]
}


What are roles?
Roles are used for granting access to an aws resource/service to access another aws resource or service of an account.
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
